Simple Harmonic Motion (SHM)

Definition (Simple Harmonic Motion Motion where the restoring force is directly proportional to the displacement from equilibrium and acts in the direction opposite to displacement.).

Energy in SHM

  • Potential energy:
  • Kinetic energy:
  • Total energy:

Energy continuously transforms between potential and kinetic:

  • At maximum displacement (): All energy is potential
  • At equilibrium position (): All energy is kinetic

Simple pendulum
Exercise (A pendulum of length 0.75 m oscillates with a small amplitude. ).

a) Calculate its period on Earth.
b) How would the period change if the pendulum were taken to the Moon, where m/s²?
c) If the amplitude is doubled, how does this affect the period (assuming small angle approximation still applies)?

Connections to Waves

  • SHM is the foundation for understanding wave behavior
  • Each particle in a wave undergoes SHM
  • Wave speed:
  • Wave types:
    - Transverse: oscillation perpendicular to wave direction
    - Longitudinal: oscillation parallel to wave direction

AP Exam Preparation Strategy

Exam Structure

  • Multiple Choice: 50 questions (90 minutes)
  • Free Response: 5 questions (90 minutes)
    • 1 experimental design
    • 1 quantitative/qualitative translation
    • 2 short answer
    • 1 paragraph argument

Five-Week Study Plan

Week Focus Area Practice
1 (Current) SHM & Waves; Review Forces 2017 FRQs
2 Energy & Momentum 2018 FRQs
3 Rotational Motion 2019 FRQs
4 Comprehensive Practice Full Practice Exam
5 Targeted Review of Weak Areas Mixed FRQs

Practice Approach

  1. Read the entire problem before starting
  2. Draw diagrams for every problem
  3. Use consistent problem-solving strategy:
    • Identify known quantities
    • Determine what's being asked
    • Select relevant principle/equation
    • Execute and check units
  4. Practice explaining concepts verbally
  5. Review mistakes carefully
Homework Total length ~ [90-120min]
  1. Simple Harmonic Motion
    • Read OpenStax Chapter 16.1-16.4
    • Watch Khan Academy video on springs and SHM
    • Problems: OpenStax Chapter 16: 1, 5, 9, 15
    • AP Problems: Openstax chapter 10: 7-14
  2. AP Exam Practice
    • Complete the 2017 AP Physics 1 FRQ #1
    • Create a one-page "cheat sheet" of key formulas and concepts for mechanics
  3. Review Activity
    • Choose one challenging topic from previous sessions
    • Create a 3-minute video explaining the concept to a classmate
    • Include at least one worked example
  4. Experiment (Optional)
    • Design and conduct a simple pendulum experiment to verify the period-length relationship
    • Document your results with photos/video and a brief analysis
